  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The governing claim requires that the relative hemolysis index remain below 1.0 across all evaluated flow-speed combinations AND that rotor tip speed must not exceed 9.5 m/s under any simulated operating condition — a constraint directly tied to erythrocyte shear-stress damage thresholds identified in the clinical risk analysis. This tip-speed ceiling is treated as a binding safety obligation throughout the assessment narrative and is referenced in the model configuration documentation.",
